    <item>
      <title>Re: Summit report from a Cleric's perspective</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9014#M9014</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;The simple solution to the "softcaps" is to just remove them completely. A tank who equips a 20 ac item, ALREADY gets more ac from the same item. Then add to that the fact that class items for tanks (Time/GoD/OOW armors) have higher ac than the quivalent items for clerics.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A cleric in full GoD quest armor, will have lower ac than a Warrior in the equivalent armor set. This is fine, good even. Going by the tanks in my guild, the difference seems to be in the 400-600ac range.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Throw in the softcap, and now, instead of being a cleric with 2100ac protecting me, I am essentially a cleric with about 1600ac. The only&amp;nbsp;clerics who get the full AC advantage of those armor sets, and the even better tacvi/anguish armors, are new apps who throw on a coule Qvic pieces, along with some bazaar gear, and end up able to take about the same damage as me, with 400-500 less ac.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Throw away sofcaps, for everyone. All classes. Robe casters will still only get one ac per worn AC, wheras plate tanks get around 2ish, and clerics get somewhere in between. Clerics still only get Dodge, and a low cap, compared to many defensive/avoidance skills for tanks.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Even with removed softcaps, clerics are not going to threaten knights as group tanks. What will happen is well geared clerics will take melee damage better than poorly geared clerics. Well geared wizards will take damage better than poorly geared wizards. Top geared tanks will get to use all of their ac, probably making an even bigger gap between tanks and clerics, but at least it will improve cleric survivability. And it will make gear matter for all classes more.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
