      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9027#M9027</link>
      <description>I just want to say, I am 100% for removing softcaps.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hidden soft caps and mitigation "tables" are probably some of the worst ideas I have ever heard in my entire gaming/programming career.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I suspect there is hesitation because eliminating softcaps for the actual tanking classes with the current formulas would trivialize too much content.  However, this re-envisioning process seems like the perfect place to me to get rid of a concept that was never really a good idea in the first place.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At the very, very least, if softcaps absolutely must stay in-game, then make the gosh darn displayed AC number be &lt;i&gt;post-softcap&lt;/i&gt;.  Hidden things are BAD BAD BAD!</description>
