    <item>
      <title>Re: Summit report from a Cleric's perspective</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=8923#M8923</link>
      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Avrel wrote:&lt;BR&gt;He was tanking that **SMURF** even before the mitigation changes came through. AA's actually do make a difference as does gear.&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Apples and oranges, I've already proven that clerics are meant to tank in some situations and you have only countered with opinion on "what is enough." This is a shady territory, because in your example, the monks, had whined relentlessly for years and advocated for a nerf repeal that finally did occur. Which again turns to subjective opinion.&amp;nbsp;Three facts:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. We get less avoidance on high end gear compared to other classes&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. AC return does not quantify avoidance return&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3. Cleric AC return equates to Shaman AC return&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Which becomes subjective to opinion and play style bias, the center piece of 90% of the Hurk vs. someone arguements. With both clerics and monks the opinions are what it comes down to, and how the developers interpret the way things "should" be. I believe it is safe to say here, that along the lines of the increased AC returns you are in the minority.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
